Aim :To make stack operaction 

Alogorithm:

1. Initialization
Read Size: Get the maximum size of the stack, MAX.
Initialize Array: Create an array, STACK, of size MAX.
Initialize Top: Set the pointer TOP = -1. (This indicates the stack is empty).
2. PUSH Operation (Inserting an Element)
This procedure adds an element to the top of the stack.
Check for Overflow:
IF TOP = MAX - 1:
The stack is full. Print "Stack Overflow" and EXIT.
Insert Element:
Read the element to be inserted, VALUE.
Increment TOP: Set TOP = TOP + 1.
Store Value: Set STACK[TOP] = VALUE.
End.
3. POP Operation (Deleting an Element)
This procedure removes the element from the top of the stack.
Check for Underflow:
IF TOP = -1:
The stack is empty. Print "Stack Underflow" and EXIT.
Retrieve Element:
Set VALUE = STACK[TOP]. (This retrieves the element at the top).
Decrement TOP:
Set TOP = TOP - 1. (This logically removes the element).
Display: Print the VALUE that was popped.
End.
4. EXIT Operation
Print: Display "Exiting Program."
Terminate: End the program execution.


code:#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
    int max;
    int top = -1;

    printf("Enter the size of the stack: ");
    scanf("%d", &max);

    int stack[max]; // Assuming C99 VLA support or similar
    int choice;
    int value;

    while (1) {
        printf("\nStack Operations Menu:\n");
        printf("1. Push\n");
        printf("2. Pop\n");
        printf("3. Exit\n");
        printf("Enter your choice: ");
        scanf("%d", &choice);

        switch (choice) {
            case 1:
                // Push operation
                if (top == max - 1) { // Stack Overflow condition
                    printf("Stack overflow! Cannot push elements.\n");
                } else {
                    printf("Enter a value to PUSH: ");
                    scanf("%d", &value);
                    top = top + 1;
                    stack[top] = value;
                    printf("Value %d pushed to stack at position %d.\n", value, top);
                }
                break;

            case 2:
                // Pop operation
                if (top == -1) { // Stack Underflow condition
                    printf("Stack underflow! Stack is empty.\n");
                } else {
                    value = stack[top];
                    top = top - 1;
                    printf("POPPED value: %d\n", value);
                }
                break;

            case 3:
                // Exit operation
                printf("Exiting Program.\n");
                return 0; // Exits the main function and program

            default:
                printf("Invalid choice.\n");
        }
    }
    return 0; 
}


out put :
Enter the size of the stack: 5

Stack Operations Menu:
1. Push
2. Pop
3. Exit
Enter your choice: 1
Enter a value to PUSH: 23
Value 23 pushed to stack at position 0.

